<br>
Your working under the basis that a series of 100 casts will result in 7 crits, where this is not the case.<br>
<br>
Each cast has a 7% chance to Crit.  This chance is calculated on each cast independantly of the other and will never &quot;add up&quot; to any set percentage in increased damage output over a givin time.<br>
<br>
It is possible, however inprobable, that you could cast all crits for a 30 min period.  The odds against that are staggering, but nothing in the game limits the amount of crits you can have in a givin amount of time, it's all luck and random numbers.<br>
<br>
Casting Fury 1/2/3, due to it's random chance of occuring, can not be used as a measure of a Wizards ability to deal sustainable damage. IMHO of course. <p>Sildiven Azuenden<BR>
30th Wizard of Agnostic!<BR><BR>
